## 1. Cabin Vibration Sources V2.0

### 1.1 Ship-Specific Vibration Profile

Cruise ships generate vibration from:
- Main diesel-electric propulsion (typical: 6-cylinder, 120 RPM diesel -> 2 Hz fundamental)
- Propeller blade passage frequency (e.g., 6-blade propeller at 120 RPM: 12 Hz)
- Auxiliary machinery (pumps, fans: 25-200 Hz range)
- Wave encounter (0.05-0.5 Hz; kinetosis-inducing for susceptible passengers)

**ISO 6954:2024 passenger comfort limits:**
| Frequency Band | Comfort Limit (rms) |
|---|---|
| 0.5-1 Hz | 7.5 mm/s |
| 1-2 Hz | 5.0 mm/s |
| 2-80 Hz | 2.8 mm/s |
| >80 Hz | 0.5 mm/s |

Many cruise ships exceed these limits at propeller blade frequency during sea state 4-5.

